\n| shorts1     = 22211D\n| socks1      = 22211D\n| pattern_la2 = _thinblackborder\n| pattern_b2  = _hyderabadfc_away_2019_20\n| pattern_ra2 = _thinblackborder\n| pattern_sh2 = _black_stripes\n| pattern_so2 = \n| leftarm2    = C1C85C\n| body2       = \n| rightarm2   = C1C85C\n| shorts2     = C1C85C\n| socks2      = C1C85C\n| updated            = 20 February 2020\n| prevseason         = \n| nextseason         = ''2020\u201321'' <!-- [[2020\u201321 Hyderabad FC season|2020\u201321]] -->\n}}\n\nThe '''2019\u201320 [[Hyderabad FC]] season''' is the first ever competitive season in the club's history and the inaugural season in the [[Indian Super League]].<ref name=\"establishment\">{{cite web|url=https://www.indiansuperleague.com/press-releases/hyderabad-fc-joins-the-hero-isl|title=Hyderabad FC joins the Hero ISL|publisher=Indian Super League|date=27 August 2019|accessdate=1 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190827211612/https://www.indiansuperleague.com/press-releases/hyderabad-fc-joins-the-hero-isl|archive-date=27 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Background ==\nThe Hyderabad FC replaced the [[FC Pune City]] in 2019 and will debut in the [[2019\u201320 Indian Super League season]]. FC Pune City was dissolved after the [[2018\u201319 Indian Super League season|2018\u201319 season]] due to prolonged financial and technical troubles. The franchise was taken over by Vijay Madduri, a Hyderabad based entrepreneur, and Varun Tripuraneni, the former CEO of the [[Kerala Blasters FC|Kerala Blasters]]. The owners decided to move the franchise to their home city of [[Hyderabad]].<ref name=\"HyderabadFC\">{{cite news|last=Sen|first=Debayan|url=https://www.espn.in/football/india/story/3929618/hyderabad-fc-to-replace-pune-city-in-isl|title=Hyderabad FC to replace Pune City in ISL|work=ESPN|date=27 August 2019|accessdate=1 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190827211617/https://www.espn.in/football/india/story/3929618/hyderabad-fc-to-replace-pune-city-in-isl|archive-date=27 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The club was announced on 27 August 2019.<ref name=\"establishment\"/> The Hyderabad FC will be the first club from [[Hyderabad]] to feature in the Indian Super League.<ref name=\"HyderabadFC\"/>\n\nThe club officially unveiled their logo on 21 September and the home jersey for their maiden season on 29 September.<ref>{{cite web |title=New ISL franchise Hyderabad Football Club unveils logo |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/indian-super-league/top-stories/new-isl-franchise-hyderabad-football-club-unveils-logo/articleshow/71237101.cms |website=Times of India|agency=Press Trust of India|accessdate=1 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190922150000/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/indian-super-league/top-stories/new-isl-franchise-hyderabad-football-club-unveils-logo/articleshow/71237101.cms |archive-date=22 September 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"HFCjersey\">{{cite news|last=|first=|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/indian-super-league/hyderabad-fc-launches-team-jersey-for-isl-season-6/articleshow/71360288.cms|title=Hyderabad FC launches team jersey for ISL season 6|website=Times of India|agency=Press Trust of India|date=29 September 2019|accessdate=1 October 2019}}</ref> The Hyderabad FC will play their home matches at [[G.M.C. Balayogi Athletic Stadium]] which has a capacity of 30,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiansuperleague.com/clubs/1536-hyderabad-fc-profile/venue|title=G.M.C Balayogi Athletic Stadium|publisher=ISL|access-date=18 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Vasudevan|first=Shyam|url=https://sportstar.thehindu.com/football/isl/isl-features/hyderabad-fc-isl-2019-20-season-preview-schedule-phil-brown-adil-khan-nestor-gordillo-robin-singh-marko-stankovic/article29716701.ece|title=ISL 2019-20: Can new-entrant Hyderabad FC banish the Pune City blues?|website=Sportstar|access-date=20 October 2019|date=18 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Kits==\n<center>\n{|\n|{{Football kit\n| pattern_la = _yellow_thin_border\n| pattern_b  = _hyderabadfc_home_2019_20\n| pattern_ra = _yellow_thin_border\n| pattern_sh = _yellow_stripes\n| pattern_so = \n| leftarm    = 22211D\n| body       = \n| rightarm   = 22211D\n| shorts     = 22211D\n| socks      = 22211D\n| title      = Home\n}}\n|{{Football kit\n| pattern_la = _thinblackborder\n| pattern_b  = _hyderabadfc_away_2019_20\n| pattern_ra = _thinblackborder\n| pattern_sh = _black_stripes\n| pattern_so = \n| leftarm    = C1C85C\n| body       = \n| rightarm   = C1C85C\n| shorts     = C1C85C\n| socks      = C1C85C\n| title      = Away\n}}\n|}\n</center>\n\n==Management team==\n{{updated|23 January 2020}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Role\n! Name\n|-\n| Head Coach\n| {{flagicon|ESP}} [[Xavier Gurri Lopez]]\n|-\n| Assistant Coach\n| {{flagicon|IND}} [[Mehrajuddin Wadoo]]\n|-\n| Head Performance Analyst \n| {{flagicon|IND}} [[Joy Gabriel]] \n|-\n|}\n\n== Players ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%; width:75%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#808080; color:#FFDF00; text-align:center;\"| No.\n! style=\"background:#808080; color:#FFDF00; text-align:center;\"| Name\n! style=\"background:#808080; color:#FFDF00; text-align:center;\"| Nationality\n! style=\"background:#808080; color:#FFDF00; text-align:center;\"| Position\n! style=\"background:#808080; color:#FFDF00; text-align:center;\"| Date of Birth\n! style=\"background:#808080; color:#FFDF00; text-align:center;\"| Signed Year\n! style=\"background:#808080; color:#FFDF00; text-align:center;\"| Previous Club\n|-\n! colspan=\"8\" style=\"background:#808080; color:#FFDF00; text-align:center;\"| Goalkeepers\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Kamaljit Singh]]\n| {{flagicon|IND}}\n| [[Goalkeeper (association football)|GK]]\n| {{birth date and age2 |df=yes|2019|10|20 |1995|12|28}}\n| 2019\n|align=\"left\"| {{flagicon|IND}} [[FC Pune City|Pune City]]\n|-\n| 33\n| [[Laxmikant K